# Studio UI — Project Structure

Studio UI is a visual design-to-code tool. Designers create screens in a browser canvas; the system compiles them to production React/Expo code.

## Monorepo Layout

```
/
├── apps/web/              Next.js app (the Studio editor)
├── compiler/              Spec-to-code compiler (Next.js + Expo emitters)
├── cli/                   Studio CLI (pnpm studio)
├── spec/
│   ├── screens/           Screen specs (*.screen.json) — the source of truth
│   ├── ds-starters/       Design system token presets
│   ├── schema/            JSON Schema for screen specs
│   ├── templates/         Component templates
│   └── page-templates/    Full-page templates
├── tokens/                Active project tokens (design-tokens.json)
├── studio.config.json     Project config (framework, paths, fonts)
└── docs/                  Release notes and architecture docs
```

## Key Config: studio.config.json

```json
{
  "framework": "nextjs",
  "screensDir": "spec/screens",
  "tokens": "tokens/design-tokens.json",
  "generatedDir": "apps/web/components/generated",
  "componentsDir": "apps/web/components/ui"
}
```

## CLI Commands (from monorepo root)

- `pnpm studio compile` — compile all screens to React components
- `pnpm studio compile <name>` — compile a single screen
- `pnpm studio lint` — lint all screen specs
- `pnpm studio lint <name>` — lint a single screen
- `pnpm studio list-screens` — list all screens with their routes
- `pnpm studio get-screen <name>` — print a screen spec as JSON
- `pnpm studio tokens` — print current design tokens

## Dev Server

The editor runs at `http://localhost:3000`. Start with:
```bash
cd apps/web && pnpm dev
```

API routes live at `/api/studio/*` (screens, tokens, compile, etc.).

## How Screens Flow

1. Designer creates/edits in the browser canvas
2. Studio saves a `.screen.json` file to `spec/screens/`
3. `pnpm studio compile` reads specs and emits React components to `apps/web/components/generated/`
4. The generated code uses the project's component library (shadcn by default)
